reviews.text: Slab Pizza's "The Meikel" is an absolute game-changer! This Thai-inspired pizza is a flavor explosion, perfectly balancing the savory richness of peanut sauce with the sweet tang of pineapple, the fresh bite of green onion and cilantro, and the smoky depth of roasted red peppers. It's a unique and incredibly delicious combination that you won't find anywhere else. Beyond the phenomenal taste, Slab Pizza consistently delivers on great prices and truly amazing service. If you're looking for an unforgettable pizza experience, "The Meikel" is a must-try!

My husband and I love slab and we don‚Äôt come as often as we would like! My husband loves the Buffalo wing. That is the only one he orders. I have tried a few different ones but one of my favorite ones is the Thai Chicken.

I enjoyed eating at this place and, while I do think their customer service and food deserve one star, this place could be better.

The food was great! The ingredients tasted fresh, they have all the condiments you need and the dough was very crispy and delicious. Although they didn't have ranch so that's not good.

I just think the building itself is pretty dead. I know the location doesn't help but it's very quiet and unlively here. This place also attracts immodest young adults that don't care about manners and cleaning up after themselves.

The restaurant itself is great. It's the location and the regular customers I have issues with.

SLAB continues to impress me each time I visit! The decor, the music, the cool college students hanging out, and the amazing food! It is tasty, satisfying and a great deal. The service is fast, friendly, and the employees are always willing to listen, help and problem solve. The owner is phenomenally positive, kind and works alongside the others to help things run smoothly. Modifications to toppings are always allowed (you want arugula & rosemary dust on top? Just ask!) and a gluten free crust is no problem here. The dining area, kitchen and bathroom are all exceptionally clean. This is even more remarkable given the sheer number of customers served daily. My nephew wrote his college application essay about SLAB pizza, and HE WAS ACCEPTED! THANKS SLAB!! Your pizza üçï is second only to your high quality service!
Always full of delicious, creative food that I can't get enough of. The food is gorgeous and wonderful. The pear salad pizza is top notch.

detailedReviews.author: Joseph Stoddard
detailedReviews.text: 10 years ago I would have given them 5 stars. The dough is different, dry, similar to the dough you get with a lunchable pizza. The Rosemary potato pizza was very dry and flavorless, the toppings were sparse which contributed to the dryness. The cheese bread was also pretty bland and flavorless. The buffalo chicken was ok, mainly the sauce hid the mediocrity of it all. The service was very lacking. This may also explain the quality of the food. The bathroom was out of toilet paper, we let the employees know and nothing was done about it the 30 more minutes we were there. Used to be a great place to eat, but I probably won‚Äôt go back any time soon, which makes me sad because it used to be one of my favorites.
